The fluorescence turn-on approach for detection of UA is based on the interaction of S,N-CDs with MnO2 nanosheets. The sensing process is shown in Scheme 1
                        . When MnO2 nanosheets are added to S,N-CD solution, the fluorescence of S,N-CDs is suppressed. In the presence of UA, MnO2 nanosheets are destroyed, which results in a recovery of the fluorescence of S,N-CDs (Fig. 4
                        ). With increasing the concentration of UA, the fluorescence intensity at 430 nm gradually increases. It should be noted that we tested some other kinds of CDs including citric acid- and glucose-derived CDs for UA sensing. The sensitivity with S,N-CDs was higher and so we chose them for method development.

Fluorescence recovery of S,N-CDs was observed immediately upon addition of UA to CDs-MnO2 nanosheets system. At this stage, the fluorescence sensor was switched to the “on” state. The fluorescence recovery may be ascribed to the redox reaction between MnO2 nanosheets and UA witch results in a partial decomposition of MnO2 nanosheets to Mn2+. MnO2/Mn2+ redox potential is 1.23 V vs SHE while the redox potential of uric acid depends on conditions and values ranging from 0.26 to 0.59 V vs SHE have been reported [35]. Anyway, inspection of UV–vis absorption spectrum of MnO2 nanosheets indicates that absorbance of nanosheets significantly decreases after addition of UA (Fig. 6
                           a). This confirms the interaction of UA with nanosheets. At higher concentrations, the absorption peaks of UA also appear and superimpose on the spectrum of MnO2 nanosheets. In Fig. 6b, we have compared the theoretical sum of absorptions spectra of UA and MnO2 nanosheets with experimental spectrum obtained for the mixture. As can be seen, absorption of UA and MnO2 nanosheets both decreases significantly in the mixture which again confirms their reaction. Moreover, TEM image of MnO2 nanosheets after reaction with UA was obtained (Fig. 7
                           ). As can be seen, upon addition of UA, nanosheets have been destroyed and converted to small pieces.
